# 4. 雪の弓道場で

Shizuku: (Don't worry... Just calm yourself and focus...)
Shizuku: (Focus only on this shot...!)
Shizuku: It hit...!
First Years: Yeah! Nice shot, Hinomori!
Second Years: Yeah, nice one! You've improved so much!
Shizuku: (I'm so glad that I practiced so much. I finally feel like a member of this club now...)
Shizuku: (And I have Asahina to thank.)
Archery Club Captain: Oh, Asahina's up next!
Shizuku: You can do it, Asahina...!
Shizuku: *Gasp* She hit the bullseye...!
Archery Club Captain: She's so focused, and her accuracy is remarkable... She might be in the running to win it all.
Shizuku: What? She has a chance to win...?!
Shizuku: (I believe in you, Asahina...!)
MC: That concludes the award ceremony.
Second Years: Man, Asahina, you were so close!
Archery Club Captain: Fourth place is more than respectable! It's hard to believe that you were just a novice not too long ago.
First Years: Does this mean Asahina's in line to become the next captain?
Archery Club Captain: Whoa, slow down. I'm standing right here...
Shizuku: Hehe...
Shizuku: (Still, Asahina was so cool today.)
Shizuku: (Despite this being her very first tournament, she produced incredible results...)
Shizuku: (She says that she isn't perfect, but...)
First Years: Wait a second. I haven't seen Asahina at all since the award ceremony ended...
Second Years: She said she needed to use the restroom, but it's been quite some time now. We need to start heading out soon...
Shizuku: Oh, then... I'll try finding her.
Archery Club Captain: You will? Thanks, Hinomori!
Shizuku: (I was hoping to find her here since she didn't seem to be in the restroom...)
Shizuku: (But I'm not seeing anyone. I suppose it's because the award ceremony just ended.)
Shizuku: Oh, Asahina...
Shizuku: (Huh...?)
Mafuyu: Oh, Hinomori, what are you doing here?
Shizuku: I, um... We need to head out soon, so I came to let you know.
Mafuyu: Oh, it's already time...? I'm sorry. I felt somewhat tired, so I decided to take a quick break.
Shizuku: Yes, I understand. The final round must've been very tense since it got so close...
Mafuyu: Yes, it was. My heart raced the entire time since I was competing against experienced archers.
Mafuyu: But I feel much better now. Let's return to where the others are, shall we?
Shizuku: Yes, let's...
Shizuku: (She must've been more tired than I realized...)
Archery Club Captain: Alright, let's wrap up practice here today! It's chilly out, so try to stay warm, everyone!
Shizuku & Mafuyu: Thank you! We will!
Shizuku: *Sigh* I need to get ready...
Mafuyu: Oh, Hinomori, do you have work after this?
Shizuku: Yes, I do. I apologize for not being able to help clean up...
Mafuyu: That's okay. You always do more than enough when you are available, so I wouldn't worry too much.
Mafuyu: Oh, the weather forecast said that it might snow today, so please be careful, Hinomori.
Shizuku: Yes, I will. Thank you, Asahina.
Shizuku: It took longer than expected to change. I need to hurry...
Shizuku: My manager's calling? Hello, this is Hinomori.
Shizuku: Oh, the interviewer came down with a cold...? That's terrible...
Shizuku: So, today's interview is going to be postponed? Understood. Thank you for letting me know.
Shizuku: That means I don't have work today... Hm...?
Shizuku: Oh, it's snowing... It's so beautiful.
Shizuku: Achoo... And so cold.
Shizuku: (Oh, that's right. I asked Asahina to clean up in my place. If I go back now, I might still be able to lend her a hand.)
Shizuku: (I wouldn't want her to catch a cold since the archery range is exposed to the open air.)
Shizuku: So, I should go help.
Shizuku: (Oh, it's so quiet...)
Shizuku: (Did everyone already go home...? But the door was unlocked...)
Shizuku: Wait, that sound...
Shizuku: Asahina...
Shizuku: (Asahina...?)
Shizuku: (That's all four...! And no misses...!)
Shizuku: (That's incredible... But at the same time...)
Shizuku: (It's a bit scary...)
Shizuku: (And she seems to be mumbling something to herself...)
Mafuyu: I have to...
Mafuyu: I have to hurry and...
Shizuku: (I can't quite make out what she's saying...)
Shizuku: (It's as if she's an entirely different person...)
Mafuyu: Whenever that happens, it can feel like the walls are closing in on you, and you hate everything...
Mafuyu: However, I think you'll be fine now that you've learned to calm your mind.
Mafuyu: I have a feeling that you'll be able to push much further ahead now.
Shizuku: (By calming yourself...)
Shizuku: (But she's already very good at that... And yet, it's almost as if...)
Mafuyu: I'm not perfect...
Shizuku: (Oh...)
Shizuku: (Does this mean something's bothering her?)
Shizuku: (Something so significant that not even her calming technique will help...)
Mafuyu: ...! Who's there?
Shizuku: *Gasp* Um, it's...
Shizuku: It's me, Asahina... My appointment for today got canceled, so I was wondering if I could help clean up...
Mafuyu: Oh, I see... Thank you for coming back.
Mafuyu: Unfortunately, I've already finished cleaning everything up, which is why I was practicing on my own.
Shizuku: Yes, I see...
Shizuku: Um, Asahina...
Mafuyu: Hm? Yes?
Shizuku: Oh...
Mafuyu: Did something happen at work...? Are you not feeling well by chance...?
Shizuku: N-No, I feel fine! It's just...
Shizuku: (She's back to being her usual self...)
Shizuku: (Did I imagine what I saw just now...?)
KAITO: <So, what happened after that...?>
Shizuku: Nothing of particular note...
Shizuku: Asahina did take a few days off here and there after that, but she seemed like her usual self...
Shizuku: So I began to believe I had imagined what I saw that day...
Shizuku: Then, I became so busy with work that I didn't have much time to think about it...
Shizuku: However, what I saw today... That expression was so similar to the one she had back then. It really seemed like something was bothering her...
Miku: <Hmm... What could be bothering her so much...?>
Shizuku: I can't say... But...
Shizuku: If something really is bothering her right now...
Shizuku: I'd like to help.
KAITO: <Why not tell her that...?>
Shizuku: What?
KAITO: <If you do wish to help her, it might be good to actually say that.>
Shizuku: B-But... What if saying that makes her feel uncomfortable...?
KAITO: <I don't think she will.>
KAITO: <It should be no different from what you've been doing until now.>
Shizuku: What I've been doing until now...?
KAITO: <Yes. You've been telling others that you're there for them.>
KAITO: <There's no way for idols to know exactly what their fans are feeling or going through, but you can tell them that they have your support...>
KAITO: <That sort of kindness can do wonders for a person in need.>
Shizuku: My kindness can help them...?
Miku: <Hehe. You always seem to know exactly what to say, KAITO!>
KAITO: <Hm? I do? I was just stating what came to mind...>
Shizuku: Thank you very much, KAITO...
Shizuku: I'll do my best to tell Asahina that I want to help and that I'm there for her.
